structure.name: Plugin System
structure.Functionality: The plugin system allows for dynamic loading and registration of plugins, enabling extensibility of the system. New event handlers or features can be added without modifying the core system logic, ensuring that the system remains modular and flexible.

structure.name: system_resource_management
structure.Functionality: This module encompasses various functionalities and tests related to asynchronous I/O operations, resource management, synchronization, and system-specific implementations across different operating systems (like Unix, Windows, OS/390, and others). It focuses on ensuring thread-safety, efficient event handling, file descriptor management, and proper interaction with system calls for networking and IPC mechanisms.

structure.name: event_loop_echo
structure.Functionality: This module handles and tests various event loop mechanisms and communication protocols. It provides a multi-protocol echo server (TCP, UDP, PIPE) and tests event loop handles like uv_idle_t, uv_check_t, and uv_timer_t.

structure.name: handle_management
structure.Functionality: This module primarily manages Windows handle types, focusing on initialization, closure, and reference counting for asynchronous I/O operations.

structure.name: Error Handling and Performance Monitoring
structure.Functionality: Error handling mechanisms capture and manage errors in a non-blocking manner through error callbacks or events. This component ensures the system can recover gracefully from failures without interrupting ongoing tasks.

structure.name: system_network_benchmark
structure.Functionality: This module focuses on system-level programming, networking, process management, and benchmarking. It includes components for handling low-level networking tasks (such as TCP, UDP, and socket operations), system-specific functionality for different platforms (e.g., Windows, Unix, and OS390), as well as performance testing and benchmarking utilities for various system operations like process spawning, file handling, and timer management.

structure.name: async_request_handler
structure.Functionality: This module manages asynchronous requests in Windows, including handling their states and dispatching them within an event loop.

structure.name: Thread Pool Management
structure.Functionality: Thread pool management handles long-running tasks, such as complex computations or blocking I/O operations, by offloading them to worker threads. This ensures the main event loop remains non-blocking and efficient while still allowing for resource-intensive operations.

structure.name: system_io_management
structure.Functionality: This module focuses on managing system-level operations in an event-driven, cross-platform context, using libuv. The module supports asynchronous I/O, system resource management, process handling, and network operations while ensuring proper event loop handling, memory management, error handling, and concurrency across different platforms.

structure.name: libuv_tests
structure.Functionality: This module includes a series of tests validating various core features of the libuv library, such as timer operations, network address resolution, user account retrieval, file descriptor error handling, socket options, process title management, and file system operations. The tests ensure correct behavior, error handling, and edge case scenarios across different system operations like TCP/UDP socket management, process and file handling, and memory allocation.

structure.name: file_copy_test
structure.Functionality: This module primarily tests the functionality of file copying, ensuring error handling, permission checks, and correct behavior across various scenarios.

structure.name: Timers and Callbacks
structure.Functionality: Timers are used to trigger events at specified intervals, while callbacks are executed when certain conditions are met. This allows for time-based events and deferred execution of code without blocking the event loop.

structure.name: network_system_tests
structure.Functionality: This module focuses on testing various networking and system functions, including UDP multicast communication in IPv6, socket address retrieval, handling user home directories, integration of libuv in embedded environments, and proper resource management during shutdown and close operations.

structure.name: libuv_fork_test
structure.Functionality: This module tests libuv behavior after a fork system call on Unix platforms, ensuring that timers, sockets, and signals function correctly in the child process.

structure.name: Asynchronous I/O Operations
structure.Functionality: This component is responsible for handling file I/O, network I/O, and directory monitoring operations asynchronously. It uses non-blocking calls to perform operations like reading, writing, and watching file systems, ensuring that the main execution thread remains available for processing other events.

structure.name: event_loop_tests
structure.Functionality: This module tests and verifies the behavior of event loops, TCP connections, and communication patterns across different protocols, ensuring correct handling of timeouts, event execution, and data transfer reliability.

structure.name: Event Loop Management
structure.Functionality: The event loop is the central component responsible for managing asynchronous I/O operations by handling various types of watchers (idle, prepare, check, timeout). It ensures that the system responds to events without blocking the main thread of execution, making it highly efficient in handling concurrent tasks such as network and file operations.

structure.name: pipe_connection_preparation
structure.Functionality: This module tests the preparation phase of a pipe connection, ensuring proper initialization and error handling before establishing the actual connection.

structure.name: src/unix/os390.c
structure.Functionality: Provides OS/390 specific functionality for managing resources like file events, network interfaces, and system queries, leveraging OS/390 specific system calls to gather hardware and system information.

structure.name: test/test-threadpool-cancel.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the cancellation of thread pool tasks in various scenarios. It ensures that the tasks can be properly canceled and resources are correctly cleaned up after cancellation, especially for long-running or blocking operations.

structure.name: test/test-pipe-sendmsg.c
structure.Functionality: This test file focuses on testing the functionality of sending file descriptors through pipes using the 'sendmsg' system call. It ensures correct transmission of file descriptors and verifies non-blocking behavior during pipe operations.

structure.name: test/test-barrier.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the synchronization mechanism provided by `uv_barrier`. It ensures that multiple threads can be properly synchronized using barriers, checking both the basic barrier functionality and edge cases like broadcasting and waiting with timeouts.

structure.name: test/test-process-title-threadsafe.c
structure.Functionality: This test ensures thread-safety when modifying and retrieving the process title using 'uv_set_process_title' and 'uv_get_process_title', verifying that concurrent calls do not cause race conditions or unexpected behavior.

structure.name: test/test-fs-event.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests `libuv`'s file system event monitoring features, ensuring that changes like file creation, deletion, and modifications trigger the appropriate event callbacks.

structure.name: src/unix/darwin-proctitle.c
structure.Functionality: This file provides functions for setting and modifying the process title on Darwin-based systems (macOS/iOS). It handles thread names for iOS and uses macOS-specific APIs for setting the process information on non-iOS platforms.

structure.name: test/test-eintr-handling.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the handling of `EINTR` (interrupt signal) errors in system calls, ensuring that system calls like `write()` are retried after being interrupted by signals.

structure.name: test/test-udp-dgram-too-big.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the scenario where a UDP datagram exceeds the maximum allowable size (e.g., 64KB). It ensures that the system properly handles oversized packets and returns appropriate errors like `UV_EMSGSIZE`.

structure.name: test/test-error.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the error message generation (`error_message`) and the conversion of system error codes to `libuv` error codes (`sys_error`), ensuring consistent error handling and messaging.

structure.name: test/test-pipe-connect-multiple.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests connecting multiple clients to a server over a pipe. It ensures that multiple client connections can be handled correctly, verifying that each client is able to connect and interact with the server through the pipe without interference.

structure.name: test/test-udp-send-immediate.c
structure.Functionality: Tests immediate UDP message sending functionality, ensuring that the client can send multiple messages ('PING' and 'PANG') and the server responds accordingly, verifying the handling of immediate sends and callback executions.

structure.name: test/test-threadpool.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the thread pool functionality provided by `libuv`, focusing on the behavior of work callbacks and completion callbacks, and the proper execution order and error handling when invalid callbacks are provided.

structure.name: test/test-udp-multicast-interface.c
structure.Functionality: Verifies UDP multicast functionality by creating a UDP server, binding it to a multicast address, and validating message sending and receiving in a multicast group scenario.

structure.name: test/test-getnameinfo.c
structure.Functionality: Tests the `uv_getnameinfo` function for converting IP addresses to hostnames and service names, including checks for both IPv4 and IPv6 address types, and handling of different address formats.

structure.name: test/test-async.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the asynchronous functionality in libuv by using `uv_async_t` and `uv_check_t`. It verifies that asynchronous events trigger the correct callback functions and ensures proper operation under concurrent conditions.

structure.name: test/test-close-order.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the order in which handles are closed within libuv. It ensures that when handles such as timers or checks are closed, the events are correctly processed in the expected order.

structure.name: test/test-random.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests libuv's random number generation capabilities, verifying that both asynchronous and synchronous random number generation functions ('uv_random') return valid and random results without any errors.

structure.name: test/test-async-null-cb.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests how libuv handles asynchronous operations with null callbacks. It ensures that even when a callback is null or improperly set, the system behaves as expected without crashing or misbehaving.

structure.name: src/win/fs-fd-hash-inl.h
structure.Functionality: Implements a hash-based file descriptor management system for Windows, facilitating efficient lookup and management of file descriptors using hash tables.

structure.name: test/test-shutdown-simultaneous.c
structure.Functionality: Verifies that simultaneous shutdown and connection operations are handled correctly, ensuring that callbacks are executed in the expected order without causing any deadlocks or race conditions.

structure.name: src/unix/internal.h
structure.Functionality: Contains low-level system-specific utilities for file descriptor operations, non-blocking I/O, signal handling, and system calls, tailored for Unix-based systems.

structure.name: src/unix/posix-hrtime.c
structure.Functionality: Provides a function to retrieve high-resolution timestamps using the 'clock_gettime' system call, returning the time in nanoseconds for precise time measurements.

structure.name: src/unix/random-sysctl-linux.c
structure.Functionality: Uses 'sysctl' system calls to obtain random data (such as UUIDs) when '/dev/urandom' or 'getrandom' are unavailable, offering a fallback mechanism for entropy generation.

structure.name: src/unix/process.c
structure.Functionality: Manages child process creation, I/O redirection, and process monitoring using 'fork' or 'posix_spawn', as well as handling process termination and callback mechanisms.

structure.name: src/unix/poll.c
structure.Functionality: Implements a polling mechanism to efficiently monitor multiple file descriptors for I/O readiness. This includes setting up and managing pollable event sources and triggering callbacks for I/O events.

structure.name: src/unix/linux-core.c
structure.Functionality: Handles system-level interactions on Linux for retrieving information such as CPU stats, memory usage, system uptime, and network interfaces, leveraging Linux-specific system calls.

structure.name: src/unix/sunos.c
structure.Functionality: Provides system-specific implementations for SunOS, including functions for gathering system resource information (CPU, memory, load) and managing event port-based operations.

structure.name: src/unix/pipe.c
structure.Functionality: Handles the creation and management of Unix domain pipes, supporting inter-process communication (IPC) via named and unnamed pipes, including file descriptor manipulation and permission handling.

structure.name: src/unix/freebsd.c
structure.Functionality: This file implements system information retrieval for FreeBSD, including memory and CPU metrics, process paths, and system load. It also contains event loop handling functions specific to FreeBSD for file and network I/O operations.

structure.name: src/unix/posix-poll.c
structure.Functionality: Implements the polling mechanism for monitoring multiple file descriptors for events using the 'poll()' system call, providing event-driven I/O operations.

structure.name: src/unix/random-devurandom.c
structure.Functionality: Implements random number generation by reading from '/dev/random' and '/dev/urandom' devices, ensuring secure random data for cryptographic operations.

structure.name: src/unix/darwin.c
structure.Functionality: This file implements system resource management for Darwin-based systems, providing functions to retrieve information such as system time, memory, CPU usage, and process path. It uses macOS-specific libraries to fetch hardware and system-related metrics.

structure.name: src/unix/no-fsevents.c
structure.Functionality: Contains stub implementations for file system event handling (like `fsevents`) that return an error, indicating that this functionality is not supported on the current platform.

structure.name: src/unix/openbsd.c
structure.Functionality: Implements system resource querying functions specific to OpenBSD, including memory usage, CPU stats, and process paths, using OpenBSD's sysctl system call interface.

structure.name: src/unix/aix-common.c
structure.Functionality: This file contains functions for obtaining process execution paths and high-resolution time on AIX systems, using system-specific functions to gather information relevant to event handling and performance monitoring.

structure.name: src/unix/loop-watcher.c
structure.Functionality: Implements multiple types of event watchers (e.g., prepare, check, idle) for the event loop, enabling the registration and management of callbacks that trigger at specific points in the event loop's lifecycle.

structure.name: src/unix/async.c
structure.Functionality: This file implements asynchronous notification mechanisms through `uv_async_t`. It supports cross-thread event communication by allowing threads to notify the event loop asynchronously and trigger appropriate callbacks.

structure.name: src/unix/linux-inotify.c
structure.Functionality: Implements file system event monitoring using `inotify` on Linux, enabling the detection of file system changes such as file creation, modification, and deletion, with appropriate event handling mechanisms.

structure.name: src/unix/thread.c
structure.Functionality: Implements thread creation, synchronization mechanisms (mutexes, condition variables, semaphores), and thread-local storage management using POSIX threads (pthreads) for cross-platform thread management.

structure.name: src/unix/random-getentropy.c
structure.Functionality: Uses the 'getentropy' system call (if available) to securely obtain random data, providing an alternative method for obtaining high-quality random numbers.

structure.name: src/unix/epoll.c
structure.Functionality: This file implements the epoll-based event notification mechanism on Linux. It provides functions for creating and managing epoll instances, handling file descriptors, and optimizing the event processing flow for efficient I/O operations.

structure.name: src/unix/random-getrandom.c
structure.Functionality: Fetches random data using the 'getrandom' system call on Linux, or dynamically loads the function on other platforms to ensure cross-platform random data retrieval.

structure.name: src/unix/udp.c
structure.Functionality: Manages UDP socket operations, including socket creation, binding, sending, and receiving datagrams, as well as supporting multicast and asynchronous event handling.

structure.name: src/unix/netbsd.c
structure.Functionality: Provides system resource management and status functions specific to the NetBSD operating system, using NetBSD-specific system calls (e.g., sysctl) for retrieving CPU, memory, and network interface information.

structure.name: src/unix/kqueue.c
structure.Functionality: Implements event notification and monitoring functionality using the `kqueue` API, allowing for efficient file system event monitoring such as file creation, modification, and deletion.

structure.name: test/test-udp-multicast-join6.c
structure.Functionality: Similar to 'test-udp-multicast-join.c', but specifically tests multicast join and communication functionality over IPv6, ensuring proper message reception and handling in an IPv6 environment.

structure.name: src/unix/spinlock.h
structure.Functionality: Implements spinlocks, providing synchronization primitives for multi-threaded environments in Unix-based systems to ensure mutual exclusion without blocking threads.

structure.name: test/test-not-writable-after-shutdown.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the behavior of a socket after a shutdown operation. It ensures that the socket is correctly marked as not writable once the shutdown process has been initiated, verifying that no further writes can occur after the socket is closed.

structure.name: src/unix/fsevents.c
structure.Functionality: This file provides file system event monitoring on macOS and iOS using the FSEvents API. It allows the registration of file and directory watchers to capture and report changes, providing event handling in the event loop.

structure.name: test/test-not-readable-nor-writable-on-read-error.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the behavior of a TCP client when a read error occurs, ensuring that the stream is marked as neither readable nor writable after an error is detected. It also verifies proper error handling and resource cleanup in case of read failures.

structure.name: test/test-tcp-close-accept.c
structure.Functionality: Validates the behavior of TCP connections when closing and accepting connections simultaneously, ensuring that the event loop and associated callbacks behave correctly when a connection is closed while accepting new connections.

structure.name: test/test-getaddrinfo.c
structure.Functionality: Tests the `uv_getaddrinfo` function for various address resolution scenarios, including synchronous and asynchronous resolution for both IPv4 and IPv6 addresses, ensuring correct callback behavior.

structure.name: test/test-default-loop-close.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the closing behavior of the default event loop (`uv_default_loop`), ensuring that callbacks (such as timers) are executed properly and the loop is closed correctly.

structure.name: test/test-delayed-accept.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the delayed acceptance of incoming connections on a TCP server, ensuring that the server properly handles connections with a delay before processing each one.

structure.name: test/test-udp-connect6.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests UDP socket operations over IPv6, ensuring that `uv_udp_connect` and related functions work correctly for IPv6 addresses, and verifying that IPv6-only scenarios are handled properly.

structure.name: test/runner-win.h
structure.Functionality: Defines a test runner for Windows systems, including process control, monitoring, and handling of test executions and results specific to the Windows environment.

structure.name: test/run-benchmarks.c
structure.Functionality: This file is responsible for initializing the platform environment and running various benchmark tests based on command-line arguments, either executing a single test or running multiple tests sequentially.

structure.name: test/test-stdio-over-pipes.c
structure.Functionality: Tests the redirection of standard input and output over pipes, verifying that data can be passed correctly between parent and child processes via pipes and that the behavior is as expected under different conditions.

structure.name: test/test-pass-always.c
structure.Functionality: This file implements a trivial test function that always passes. It is used to ensure that the testing framework is functioning correctly and can handle simple cases where the expected outcome is always a pass.

structure.name: test/test-udp-mmsg.c
structure.Functionality: Tests the functionality of UDP message sending and receiving with multiple message support, validating memory management and correct callback execution during the sending and receiving process.

structure.name: test/test-loop-stop.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the stop behavior of the event loop in libuv. It ensures that the loop stops correctly after executing pending callbacks and tasks, validating the proper sequence of stop and callback operations.

structure.name: test/test-get-currentexe.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the `uv_exepath` function, verifying that it correctly retrieves the path of the currently executing program, even when the process title is changed.

structure.name: test/test-idna.c
structure.Functionality: Verifies the correct functionality of IDNA (Internationalized Domain Name) processing, including UTF-8 decoding and ASCII conversion, ensuring correct handling of domain names with non-ASCII characters.

structure.name: test/test-loop-configure.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the configuration of the event loop in libuv, specifically the ability to block certain signals and adjust loop settings. It validates the correct handling of these configurations in the event loop, including ensuring proper updates to timeouts and callback executions.

structure.name: test/test-pipe-connect-error.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the behavior of connecting to a pipe with an invalid path. It ensures that the connection attempt fails and the appropriate error callback is triggered, verifying that error handling works as expected when attempting to connect to a non-existent or invalid pipe.

structure.name: test/test-multiple-listen.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests multiple listeners on the same port using `uv_listen` to handle multiple incoming client connections. It checks that multiple clients can connect and that their respective callbacks are correctly invoked for each connection.

structure.name: test/test-udp-multicast-ttl.c
structure.Functionality: Validates the correct behavior of UDP multicast with the testing of TTL (Time-to-Live) settings, verifying that the TTL value is properly applied during data transmission and ensuring correct message handling.

structure.name: test/test-poll-oob.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the handling of Out-Of-Band (OOB) data in TCP sockets, validating that OOB data can be properly received and processed while using 'uv_poll_t' to monitor socket events.

structure.name: src/win/atomicops-inl.h
structure.Functionality: Provides inline functions for atomic operations on Windows, supporting atomic manipulation of data types like integers and ensuring thread-safe execution.

structure.name: test/test-semaphore.c
structure.Functionality: Tests the functionality of semaphores and mutexes within libuv, verifying basic operations such as initialization, waiting, and releasing across multiple threads for synchronization.

structure.name: test/test-socket-buffer-size.c
structure.Functionality: Tests the behavior of socket receive buffer size settings for both TCP and UDP sockets, ensuring that the buffer size can be configured correctly and retrieved as expected across different platforms.

structure.name: test/test-poll-close-doesnt-corrupt-stack.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the behavior of closing 'uv_poll_t' handles on Windows platforms, ensuring that the stack integrity is maintained after closing the poll handles and no corruption occurs.

structure.name: test/test-gethostname.c
structure.Functionality: Verifies the behavior of the `uv_os_gethostname` function, testing valid hostname retrieval, buffer overflow scenarios, and invalid input handling.

structure.name: test/test-test-macros.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the behavior of various macros in the project, specifically string comparison and variable increment macros, using assertions like ASSERT_STR_EQ, ASSERT_STR_NE, and ASSERT_EQ to verify their correctness in different conditions.

structure.name: test/test-udp-connect.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the connection and data transmission for UDP sockets. It verifies that UDP sockets can successfully connect, send, and receive data, as well as handle errors gracefully.

structure.name: test/benchmark-thread.c
structure.Functionality: This file benchmarks the performance of thread creation and destruction. It spawns 20,000 threads and measures the time taken for their creation, calculating the number of threads created per second.

structure.name: test/test-tty-duplicate-key.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the handling of terminal (TTY) input, specifically for duplicate key events and special key sequences. It ensures that key events are properly processed and that the behavior is consistent across different platforms and input types.

structure.name: test/test-gettimeofday.c
structure.Functionality: Validates the functionality of `uv_gettimeofday`, ensuring it returns accurate system time and handles buffer sizes and invalid input gracefully.

structure.name: test/benchmark-tcp-write-batch.c
structure.Functionality: This file implements a performance benchmark that tests the efficiency of TCP write operations by sending a batch of 1 million write requests to a server and measuring the time taken for the operations.

structure.name: test/test-process-priority.c
structure.Functionality: This test verifies that the 'uv_os_setpriority' and 'uv_os_getpriority' functions correctly set and retrieve process priorities, ensuring correct behavior of priority changes across different platforms.

structure.name: test/test-readable-on-eof.c
structure.Functionality: This test checks that a socket remains readable after receiving an EOF signal, ensuring that the system correctly handles reading operations after a connection has been closed.

structure.name: src/unix/darwin-stub.h
structure.Functionality: Defines platform-specific structures and types for macOS, handling compatibility issues with system libraries like Core Foundation and File System Events.

structure.name: src/unix/pthread-fixes.c
structure.Functionality: Fixes issues with 'pthread_sigmask' on older versions of Android (pre-4.1) by using 'sigprocmask' as a replacement, ensuring signal masking functions correctly on these systems.

structure.name: test/test-close-fd.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the behavior of file descriptors in libuv, particularly focusing on the closing of file descriptors and ensuring that proper cleanup occurs after a file descriptor is closed, preventing resource leaks.

structure.name: test/test-fail-always.c
structure.Functionality: This file forces a failure during execution (using the `FATAL` macro) to test the robustness of the testing framework and error handling mechanism.

structure.name: test/test-connection-fail.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests libuv's behavior when a TCP connection attempt fails. It verifies that connection failure triggers the appropriate error handling mechanisms and callbacks, ensuring proper failure handling in the event of network issues.

structure.name: test/test-poll-multiple-handles.c
structure.Functionality: This test case checks if multiple 'uv_poll_t' handles can poll the same file descriptor without interference, ensuring proper event handling for multiple simultaneous poll operations on different handles.

structure.name: test/test-tcp-close-reset.c
structure.Functionality: Tests the behavior of TCP connection resets and closure, ensuring that connections are properly reset and closed without issues, and that callbacks are triggered in the expected order.

structure.name: test/test-timer-again.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the behavior of repeated timers using `uv_timer_again`. It ensures that timers can be reset and scheduled to run again, verifying the proper sequence of events and state transitions when a timer is restarted.

structure.name: test/test-pipe-getsockname.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the functionality of `uv_pipe_getsockname` and `uv_pipe_getpeername` functions. It ensures that the correct socket names and peer names are retrieved for a pipe, verifying the proper management of pipe socket addresses in different scenarios.

structure.name: test/test-strtok.c
structure.Functionality: Tests the custom string tokenization function `uv__strtok`, validating its functionality in splitting strings into tokens based on different delimiters, and ensuring it handles edge cases and errors correctly.

structure.name: test/test-pipe-bind-error.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests error handling when attempting to bind a pipe to an invalid or already occupied address. It ensures that errors are properly raised and handled when binding pipes fails, verifying correct behavior under error conditions.

structure.name: test/test-handle-fileno.c
structure.Functionality: Tests the interaction between libuv handles and file descriptors using the `uv_fileno` function, verifying correct file descriptor retrieval for different handle types like TCP, UDP, and TTY.

structure.name: test/test-condvar.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the functionality of `uv_cond_t` (condition variables) in libuv. It ensures proper thread synchronization by testing signaling, waiting, and broadcasting among threads under different conditions.

structure.name: test/test-udp-create-socket-early.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the creation of UDP sockets before binding them to a specific address. It ensures that attempting to bind multiple sockets or bind to unsupported address families is handled correctly by `libuv`.

structure.name: src/unix/atomic-ops.h
structure.Functionality: Implements atomic operations for Unix-based systems, providing low-level functions like compare-and-swap and CPU relaxation, critical for synchronization in multi-threaded environments.

structure.name: test/test-tcp-writealot.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests TCP socket operations, particularly focusing on the ability to send large amounts of data over a TCP connection. It ensures that connection handling, data transmission, and socket lifecycle management are functioning correctly under heavy load scenarios.

structure.name: test/test-ipc-send-recv.c
structure.Functionality: Verifies the functionality of IPC communication using pipes and sockets, ensuring correct sending and receiving of messages across processes, including both regular and edge cases.

structure.name: test/test-run-once.c
structure.Functionality: This test case ensures that 'uv_run' with the 'UV_RUN_ONCE' flag runs the event loop once and processes all pending events before returning, verifying that event handling behaves correctly for single-cycle event loop runs.

structure.name: test/test-get-memory.c
structure.Functionality: Tests the functionality of retrieving system memory details such as available memory, total memory, and restricted memory, ensuring correct behavior across different platforms.

structure.name: test/run-tests.c
structure.Functionality: This file manages the execution of a series of tests in libuv. It processes command-line arguments to run specific tests, provides test execution flow, and prints the results or errors encountered.

structure.name: test/test-metrics.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the metric tracking functionality in libuv, particularly related to idle time and I/O operations. It verifies that the metrics, such as idle time calculation, are correctly measured and reported across different scenarios.

structure.name: test/test-ip4-addr.c
structure.Functionality: Verifies the functionality of `uv_ip4_addr` and `uv_inet_ntop` functions for handling IPv4 address conversion, including testing for proper parsing and formatting of IPv4 addresses.

structure.name: test/test-tty.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests various terminal (TTY) interactions, including terminal initialization, mode changes (raw mode), and window size handling. It ensures that terminal features work correctly across different operating systems (Unix and Windows).

structure.name: test/test-thread.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests basic threading operations such as thread creation, thread-local storage (TLS), and stack sizes. It ensures that the threading features provided by the `libuv` library are functioning as expected.

structure.name: test/test-poll-close.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the proper callback triggering when closing multiple 'uv_poll_t' handles, ensuring that event-driven poll handles are correctly managed, and callbacks are called as expected when closing handles.

structure.name: test/test-udp-ipv6.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests UDP socket operations specifically for IPv6, ensuring that the library can send and receive data over IPv6 networks, and correctly handles the transition between IPv4 and IPv6 communication.

structure.name: test/test-mutexes.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests various synchronization mechanisms, including mutexes, recursive mutexes, and read-write locks in libuv. It validates the correct functionality of these locks for thread synchronization, ensuring proper locking, unlocking, and concurrent access control.

structure.name: test/test-loop-close.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests the behavior of closing the event loop in libuv. It ensures that the loop cannot be closed while tasks are still pending and that it can be successfully closed after completing the scheduled tasks. It also checks the correct shutdown process when tasks are queued.

structure.name: test/test-poll.c
structure.Functionality: This file tests basic functionality of 'uv_poll_t' in handling socket events such as reading, writing, and closing sockets. It also ensures proper management of socket events and callbacks in libuv's event loop.

structure.name: test/runner.h
structure.Functionality: Defines the general framework for running tests and benchmarks, including task management, process initialization, and result collection for both Unix and Windows systems, ensuring cross-platform compatibility.

structure.name: test/runner-win.c
structure.Functionality: This file implements platform-specific functionality for Windows. It manages the creation and management of processes, handles output capturing, and ensures proper termination of processes during test runs on Windows systems.
